# An adherent of [[Judaism]].
# A person born of a Jewish mother;
# A person of Jewish ethnicity regardless of professed religious beliefs (See [[secular Jew]]).

====Usage note====

The question of "who is a Jew" is the subject of much discussion in the Jewish community. Which definition is appropriate is highly dependent on context.

Some uses of the term "Jew" are tainted by historic anti-Jewish bigotry. The correct adjectival form is "Jewish"; the use of "Jew" as an adjective (as in "Jew lawyer" rather than "Jewish lawyer") is associated with bigotry. The use of "Jew" or "jew" as a verb (as in "to jew someone down", to bargain for a lower price) is generally seen as an extremely offensive expression based on stereotypes. <ref name="Wikipedia">From Wikipedia’s article [[w:Jew|Jew]].</ref>

